snippet.title: Panama's outgoing president touts wife's candidacy
snippet.description: She's a political novice with a scant presence on the campaign trail, but Marta Linares has one vote that matters more than most in her bid to become Panama's next vice president: that of her husband, outgoing President Ricardo Martinelli.

snippet.title: Jokes are out as South Korea mourns ferry victims
snippet.description: Jokes and concerts are out. So are school field trips and boisterous cheering at baseball games.

snippet.title: HBO's John Oliver recognizes debt to Jon Stewart
snippet.description: When the time comes for a young bird to leave the nest, he's often more than ready to go and doesn't care too much what Papa Bird thinks.

snippet.title: Why the marijuana issue is only going to get bigger
snippet.description: Pot is going to increase prominence -- and electoral importance -- in a few short years.

snippet.title: Lupita Nyong'o named People's Most Beautiful Woman in the World
snippet.description: Her film debut in "12 Years a Slave" has earned her an Oscar for best supporting actress, a Screen Actors Guild Award and an NAACP Image Award for outstanding performance by a female actor in a supporting role - plus 2014 Golden Globe and BAFTA nominations. In addition to her work on screen, Nyong'o continues to impress with some of the season's best red-carpet looks.
